latestPosts.caption:
#ELLEPartnerFeature: Tara Sutaria (@tarasutaria), known for her elegant yet approachable style, is the perfect muse for FITOOR, by Mahima Mahajan (@mahimamahajanofficial). The actress emphasises the importance of feeling comfortable in your own skin when dressing up for a special occasion—whether it’s a wedding or a festive celebration. “If you are wearing something that you are comfortable in, you will be happy, which is very important when you dress up,” Sutaria shares. Her approach to fashion aligns beautifully with FITOOR’s ethos—celebrating individual style, confidence, and effortless glamour. Tara’s partnership with Mahima Mahajan, the designer behind FITOOR, is a natural one, as both embody the same values of authenticity and femininity.

latestPosts.caption: How people greet me at parties ☹️

And today is also 5 years since my film Marjaavaan released… Unbeknownst to many, Marjaavaan saw wonderful success with its music, specifically our ballad “ Tum Hi Aana “ sung by the glorious Jubin Nautiyal, and the story connected very well with the masses - a sweet spot we were happy to hit! 

It is also a special one for me because somehow, even now, when I travel both in India and abroad - whether it’s been London, the Maldives, Nepal, Paris or New York … people stop me to chat or ask for a photograph with ‘ Zoya ‘ , not Tara :) Which I have to say is very, very sweet… Thank you so much for the love for our film and to my character… ♥️✨
